cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of semantic scene completion, which involves both computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper proposes a novel network architecture that uses gated recurrent units, which are commonly used in natural language processing, to fuse information from RGB and depth images. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
